Description:
------------

This example is part of BAT. It will only run if BAT is correctly
installed on the system.

The example shows how to use the graph fitter which comes with BAT. It
fits a straight line to a graph assuming Gaussian uncertainties for
each measured point.

The source file(s) contain(s) plenty of comments and explanations.
For further information, see the manual at

https://bat.github.io/bat-docs/master/manual/html/


Files:
------

  README                      - this file
  graphFitterSimpleExample.C  - the source code of the main program


Running the example:
--------------------

1. Make sure that BAT is correctly installed in the system.

2. Run the macro in a ROOT session, e.g., with 'root graphFitterSimpleExample.C'
